org.jconfigurations.configurators

Interface Configurator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseConfigurator, BasicConfigurator, CollectionConfigurator, JConfigurator, MapConfigurator, NoOpConfigurator, RequiredConfigurator

    public interface Configurator
     A Configurator assigns values to fields annotated with Configuration 
 of any arbritrary object.
 These values are (typically) picked up from a ConfigurationSource and 
 converted to an instance of the right type before 
 assigning the result to the field.
 Fields NOT annotated with Configuration are ignored.
    Author:
    George Aristy
